	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There is compatibility, but not direct comparibility. For direct compatibility you have to use a TNROM board, that only a few japanese games (including FF3) used.
<br />
<br />SMB2 is half compartible but you'll have to replace CHRROM with CHRRAM. The persistant false information is that only SMB2 is compatible wich is wrong. Many games would be compatible just as SMB2 is no more no less.
<br />And the number of pins has nothing to do with the revision of the game, but with the revision of it's PCB.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


